References: <1442508237.5399.119.camel@physik.uni-freiburg.de>
Message-ID: <1442509885251.80777@jhu.edu>

This is a major restriction with complex-step derivatives - it can only apply to functions whose computer implementation extends their domain to complex numbers.  I don't see how this can be done in a straightforward manner for ODEs, PDEs, quadratures, and other complicated numerical analysis techniques.
Best,
Ravi
